			<dt>Why does it depend on OS-specific knowledge?</dt>
			<dt class="noq">Shouldn't it be written in portable C?</dt>
			<dd>
				<p>It is written in portable C, however your OS's system
					headers are probably not.
					TenDRA needs to parse these during installation as part
					of its <a href="#TODO">API building</a>.</p>

				<p>Operating systems tend to have non-standard constructs in
					their headers for various reasons:
					compiler-specific features;
					unimplemented regions;
					errors; or being written in a dialect newer than TenDRA
					currently understands.
					TenDRA deals with these by providing glue which maps any
					incompatibilities to standard interfaces.
					See <a href="#TODO">the porting guide</a> for details.</p>
			</dd>

